Introduction:
Following along with Chapter 7 of Introduction to Statistical Learning First Edition from www.statlearning.com.

Exercise #8:
Fit some of the non-linear models investigated in this chapter to the Auto data set. Is there evidence for non-linear relationships in this data set? Create some informative plots to justify your answer.

Initial data exploration:

library(GGally)
library(ISLR)
pairs(Auto)
It would appear that the correlation between MPG and seemingly everything is non-linear. 


ggplot(Auto, aes(x = displacement, y = mpg)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.5) +
  geom_smooth()

ggplot(Auto, aes(x = horsepower, y = mpg)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.5) +
  geom_smooth()

ggplot(Auto, aes(x = weight, y = mpg)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.5) +
  geom_smooth()

ggplot(Auto, aes(x = acceleration, y = mpg)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.5) +
  geom_smooth()

ggplot(Auto, aes(x = year, y = mpg)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.5) +
  geom_smooth()

Answer:
I would definetly say theres non linear relationships in this data. All of those graphs are clearly non linear. Especially the mpg x acceleration (second from bottom).
